#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:216
msgid ""
"Before continuing, you need to set up access to your cluster. As with the "
"setup of the cluster itself, how you configure DNS will be different "
"depending on where it is being hosted."
msgstr ""
"在继续之前，需要设置群集访问权限。与群集本身的设置一样，DNS 的配置方式根据群"
"集的托管位置而异。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><tip><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:217
msgid ""
"If you do not want to handle setting up DNS records (for example, this is "
"just an ephemeral test server), you can use a service like <link xl:href="
"\"https://sslip.io\">sslip.io</link> instead. With this service, you can "
"resolve any IP address with <literal>&lt;address&gt;.sslip.io</literal>."
msgstr ""
"如果您不想处理 DNS 记录的设置（例如，这只是一个临时使用的测试服务器），可以改"
"用 <link xl:href=\"https://sslip.io\">sslip.io</link> 之类的服务。通过此服"
"务，可以使用 <literal>&lt;address&gt;.sslip.io</literal> 解析任何 IP 地址。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:219
msgid ""
"To install Rancher, you need to get access to the Kubernetes API of the "
"cluster you just created. This looks differently depending on what "
"distribution of Kubernetes is being used."
msgstr ""
"要安装 Rancher，需要访问刚刚创建的群集的 Kubernetes API。具体方法取决于使用"
"的 Kubernetes 发行版。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:220
msgid ""
"For RKE2, the kubeconfig file will have been written to <literal>/etc/"
"rancher/rke2/rke2.yaml</literal>.  Save this file as <literal>~/.kube/"
"config</literal> on your local system.  You may need to edit the file to "
"include the correct externally routable IP address or host name."
msgstr ""
"对于 RKE2，kubeconfig 文件会写入 <literal>/etc/rancher/rke2/rke2.yaml</"
"literal>。将此文件作为 <literal>~/.kube/config</literal> 保存在本地系统上。可"
"能需要编辑该文件，以包含正确的外部可路由 IP 地址或主机名。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:221
msgid ""
