"management. Usually, this network is also connected to a separate management "
"switch, but it can be connected to the same service switch using VLANs to "
"isolate the traffic."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">管理网络</emphasis>：此网络用于管理 ATIP 节点。它用"
"于带外管理。通常，此网络还会连接到独立的管理交换机，但可以通过 VLAN 连接到同"
"一服务交换机以隔离流量。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2026
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Control-plane network</emphasis>: This network is "
"used for the communication between the ATIP nodes and the services that are "
"running on them. This network is also used for the communication between the "
"ATIP nodes and the external services, like the <literal>DHCP</literal> or "
"<literal>DNS</literal> servers. In some cases, for connected environments, "
"the switch/router can handle traffic through the Internet."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">控制平面网络</emphasis>：此网络用于 ATIP 节点与其上"
"运行的服务之间的通讯。此网络还用于 ATIP 节点与外部服务（例如 <literal>DHCP</"
"literal> 或 <literal>DNS</literal> 服务器）之间的通讯。在某些情况下，对于联网"
"环境，交换机/路由器可以通过互联网处理流量。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2027
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Other networks</emphasis>: In some cases, the ATIP "
"nodes could be connected to other networks for specific customer purposes."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">其他网络</emphasis>：在某些情况下，ATIP 节点可以连"
"接到其他网络以满足特定的客户目的。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2028
msgid ""
"To use the directed network provisioning workflow, the management cluster "
"must have network connectivity to the downstream cluster server Baseboard "
"Management Controller (BMC) so that host preparation and provisioning can be "
"automated."
msgstr ""
"要使用定向网络置备工作流程，管理群集必须与下游群集服务器基板管理控制器 (BMC) "
"建立网络连接，以便可以自动准备和置备主机。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2029
msgid "Services (DHCP, DNS, etc.)"
msgstr "服务（DHCP、DNS 等）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2030
msgid ""
"Some external services like <literal>DHCP</literal>, <literal>DNS</literal>, "
"etc. could be required depending on the kind of environment where they are "
"deployed:"
msgstr ""
"可能需要一些外部服务（例如 <literal>DHCP</literal>、<literal>DNS</literal> "
"等），具体取决于部署环境的类型："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2031
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Connected environment</emphasis>: In this case, "
"the ATIP nodes will be connected to the Internet (via routing L3 protocols) "
"and the external services will be provided by the customer."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">联网环境</emphasis>：在这种情况下，ATIP 节点将连接"
"到互联网（通过路由 L3 协议），外部服务将由客户提供。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2032
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Disconnected / air-gap environment</emphasis>: In "
"this case, the ATIP nodes will not have Internet IP connectivity and "
"additional services will be required to locally mirror content required by "
"the ATIP directed network provisioning workflow."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">离线/隔离环境</emphasis>：在这种情况下，ATIP 节点未"
"建立互联网 IP 连接，因此需要通过其他服务在本地镜像 ATIP 定向网络置备工作流程"
"所需的内容。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2033
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">File server</emphasis>: A file server is used to "
"store the ISO images to be provisioned on the ATIP nodes during the directed "
"network provisioning workflow. The <literal>metal<superscript>3</"
"superscript></literal> Helm chart can deploy a media server to store the ISO "
"images — check the following section (<xref linkend=\"metal3-media-server\"/"
">), but it is also possible to use an existing local webserver."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">文件服务器</emphasis>：文件服务器用于在执行定向网络"
"置备工作流程期间存储 ATIP 节点上置备的 ISO 映像。"
"<literal>metal<superscript>3</superscript></literal> Helm chart 可以部署媒体"
"服务器来存储 ISO 映像 — 请查看下面一节（<xref linkend=\"metal3-media-server"
"\"/>），但也可以使用现有的本地 Web 服务器。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2034
msgid "Disabling rebootmgr"
msgstr "禁用 rebootmgr"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2035
msgid ""
"<literal>rebootmgr</literal> is a service which allows to configure a "
"strategy for reboot when the system has pending updates.  For Telco "
"workloads, it is really important to disable or configure properly the "
"<literal>rebootmgr</literal> service to avoid the reboot of the nodes in "
"case of updates scheduled by the system, to avoid any impact on the services "
"running on the nodes."
msgstr ""
"<literal>rebootmgr</literal> 是当系统中存在未完成的更新时用于配置重引导策略的"
"服务。对于电信工作负载，必须禁用或正确配置 <literal>rebootmgr</literal> 服"
"务，以避免在系统安排了更新时重引导节点，从而避免对节点上运行的服务造成任何影"
"响。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2036
msgid ""
"For more information about <literal>rebootmgr</literal>, see <link xl:href="
"\"https://github.com/SUSE/rebootmgr\">rebootmgr GitHub repository</link>."
msgstr ""
"有关 <literal>rebootmgr</literal> 的详细信息，请参见 <link xl:href=\"https://"
"github.com/SUSE/rebootmgr\">rebootmgr GitHub 储存库</link>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2037
msgid "Verify the strategy being used by running:"
msgstr "运行以下命令来校验使用的策略："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2038
msgid "and you could disable it by running:"
msgstr "可以运行以下命令来禁用 rebootmgr："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2039
msgid "or using the <literal>rebootmgrctl</literal> command:"
msgstr "也可以使用 <literal>rebootmgrctl</literal> 命令："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2040
msgid ""
"This configuration to set the <literal>rebootmgr</literal> strategy can be "
"automated using the directed network provisioning workflow. For more "
"information, check the ATIP Automated Provisioning documentation (<xref "
"linkend=\"atip-automated-provisioning\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"可以使用定向网络置备工作流程来自动执行此项设置 <literal>rebootmgr</literal> "
"策略的配置。有关详细信息，请查看 ATIP 自动置备文档（<xref linkend=\"atip-"
"automated-provisioning\"/>）。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2041
msgid "Setting up the management cluster"
msgstr "设置管理群集"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2043
msgid ""
"The management cluster is the part of ATIP that is used to manage the "
"provision and lifecycle of the runtime stacks.  From a technical point of "
"view, the management cluster contains the following components:"
msgstr ""
"管理群集是用于管理运行时堆栈的置备和生命周期的 ATIP 组成部分。从技术角度讲，"
"管理群集包含以下组件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2044
msgid ""
"<literal>SUSE Linux Enterprise Micro</literal> as the OS. Depending on the "
"use case, some configurations like networking, storage, users and kernel "
"arguments can be customized."
msgstr ""
"<literal>SUSE Linux Enterprise Micro</literal>（操作系统）。可以根据用例自定"
"义某些配置，例如网络、存储、用户和内核参数。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2045
msgid ""
"<literal>RKE2</literal> as the Kubernetes cluster. Depending on the use "
"case, it can be configured to use specific CNI plugins, such as "
"<literal>Multus</literal>, <literal>Cilium</literal>, etc."
msgstr ""
"<literal>RKE2</literal>（Kubernetes 群集）。可以根据用例将其配置为使用特定的 "
"CNI 插件，例如 <literal>Multus</literal>、<literal>Cilium</literal> 等。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2046
msgid ""
"<literal>Rancher</literal> as the management platform to manage the "
"lifecycle of the clusters."
msgstr "<literal>Rancher</literal>（管理平台），用于管理群集的生命周期。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2047
msgid ""
"<literal>Metal<superscript>3</superscript></literal> as the component to "
"manage the lifecycle of the bare-metal nodes."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Metal<superscript>3</superscript></literal>，该组件用于管理裸机节点"
"的生命周期。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2048
msgid ""
"<literal>CAPI</literal> as the component to manage the lifecycle of the "
"Kubernetes clusters (downstream clusters). With ATIP, also the <literal>RKE2 "
"CAPI Provider</literal> is used to manage the lifecycle of the RKE2 clusters "
"(downstream clusters)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>CAPI</literal>，该组件用于管理 Kubernetes 群集（下游群集）的生命周"
"期。在 ATIP 中，<literal>RKE2 CAPI 提供程序</literal>也用于管理 RKE2 群集（下"
"游群集）的生命周期。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2049
msgid ""
"With all components mentioned above, the management cluster can manage the "
"lifecycle of downstream clusters, using a declarative approach to manage the "
"infrastructure and applications."
msgstr ""
"通过上述所有组件，管理群集可以管理下游群集的生命周期，并使用声明性方法来管理"
"基础架构和应用程序。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2050
msgid ""
"For more information about <literal>SUSE Linux Enterprise Micro</literal>, "
"see: SLE Micro (<xref linkend=\"components-slmicro\"/>)"
msgstr ""
"有关 <literal>SUSE Linux Enterprise Micro</literal> 的详细信息，请参见：SLE "
"Micro（<xref linkend=\"components-slmicro\"/>）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2051
msgid ""
"For more information about <literal>RKE2</literal>, see: RKE2 (<xref linkend="
"\"components-rke2\"/>)"
msgstr ""
"有关 <literal>RKE2</literal> 的详细信息，请参见：RKE2（<xref linkend="
"\"components-rke2\"/>）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2052
msgid ""
"For more information about <literal>Rancher</literal>, see: Rancher (<xref "
"linkend=\"components-rancher\"/>)"
msgstr ""
"有关 <literal>Rancher</literal> 的详细信息，请参见：Rancher（<xref linkend="
"\"components-rancher\"/>）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2053
msgid ""
"For more information about <literal>Metal<superscript>3</superscript></"
"literal>, see: Metal3 (<xref linkend=\"components-metal3\"/>)"
msgstr ""
"有关 <literal>Metal<superscript>3</superscript></literal> 的详细信息，请参"
"见：Metal3（<xref linkend=\"components-metal3\"/>）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2054
msgid "Steps to set up the management cluster"
msgstr "设置管理群集的步骤"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2055
msgid ""
"The following steps are necessary to set up the management cluster (using a "
"single node):"
msgstr "需要执行以下步骤来设置管理群集（使用单个节点）："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informalfigure><mediaobject>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2056
msgid ""
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"product-atip-mgmtcluster1.png\" width="
"\"\"/> </imageobject>"
msgstr ""
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"product-atip-mgmtcluster1.png\" width="
"\"\"/> </imageobject>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informalfigure><mediaobject><textobject><phrase>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2057
msgid "product atip mgmtcluster1"
msgstr "ATIP 产品管理群集 1"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2058
msgid ""
"The following are the main steps to set up the management cluster using a "
"declarative approach:"
msgstr "使用声明性方法设置管理群集需要执行以下主要步骤："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2059
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Image preparation for connected environments "
"(<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-image-preparation-connected\"/>)</emphasis>: "
"The first step is to prepare the manifests and files with all the necessary "
"configurations to be used in connected environments."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">为联网环境准备映像（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-"
"image-preparation-connected\"/>）</emphasis>：第一步是准备包含所有必要配置的"
"清单和文件，以便在联网环境中使用。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2060
msgid ""
"Directory structure for connected environments (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-"
"directory-structure\"/>): This step creates a directory structure to be used "
"by Edge Image Builder to store the configuration files and the image itself."
msgstr ""
"联网环境的目录结构（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-directory-structure\"/>）："
"此步骤创建一个目录结构，供 Edge Image Builder 用来存储配置文件和映像本身。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2061
msgid ""
"Management cluster definition file (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-image-"
"definition-file\"/>): The <literal>mgmt-cluster.yaml</literal> file is the "
"main definition file for the management cluster. It contains the following "
"information about the image to be created:"
msgstr ""
"管理群集定义文件（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-image-definition-file\"/>）："
"<literal>mgmt-cluster.yaml</literal> 文件是管理群集的主定义文件。其中包含有关"
"所要创建的映像的以下信息："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2062
msgid ""
"Image Information: The information related to the image to be created using "
"the base image."
msgstr "映像信息：与要使用基础映像创建的映像相关的信息。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2063
msgid ""
"Operating system: The operating system configurations to be used in the "
"image."
msgstr "操作系统：要在映像中使用的操作系统配置。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2064
msgid ""
"Kubernetes: Helm charts and repositories, kubernetes version, network "
"configuration, and the nodes to be used in the cluster."
msgstr ""
"Kubernetes：要在群集中使用的 Helm chart 和储存库、Kubernetes 版本、网络配置以"
"及节点。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2065
msgid ""
"Custom folder (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-custom-folder\"/>): The "
"<literal>custom</literal> folder contains the configuration files and "
"scripts to be used by Edge Image Builder to deploy a fully functional "
"management cluster."
msgstr ""
"Custom 文件夹（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-custom-folder\"/>）："
"<literal>custom</literal> 文件夹包含的配置文件和脚本供 Edge Image Builder 用"
"来部署功能完备的管理群集。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2066
msgid ""
"Files: Contains the configuration files to be used by the management cluster."
msgstr "Files 文件夹：包含管理群集要使用的配置文件。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2067
msgid "Scripts: Contains the scripts to be used by the management cluster."
msgstr "Scripts 文件夹：包含管理群集要使用的脚本。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2068
msgid ""
"Kubernetes folder (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-kubernetes-folder\"/>): The "
"<literal>kubernetes</literal> folder contains the configuration files to be "
"used by the management cluster."
msgstr ""
"Kubernetes 文件夹（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-kubernetes-folder\"/>）："
"<literal>kubernetes</literal> 文件夹包含管理群集要使用的配置文件。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2069
msgid "Manifests: Contains the manifests to be used by the management cluster."
msgstr "Manifests 文件夹：包含管理群集要使用的清单。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2070
msgid "Helm: Contains the Helm charts to be used by the management cluster."
msgstr "Helm 文件夹：包含管理群集要使用的 Helm chart。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2071
msgid ""
"Config: Contains the configuration files to be used by the management "
"cluster."
msgstr "Config 文件夹：包含管理群集要使用的配置文件。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2072
msgid ""
"Network folder (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-network-folder\"/>): The "
"<literal>network</literal> folder contains the network configuration files "
"to be used by the management cluster nodes."
msgstr ""
"Network 文件夹（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-network-folder\"/>）："
"<literal>network</literal> 文件夹包含管理群集节点要使用的网络配置文件。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2073
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Image preparation for air-gap environments (<xref "
"linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-image-preparation-airgap\"/>)</emphasis>: The step is "
"to show the differences to prepare the manifests and files to be used in an "
"air-gap scenario."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">为隔离环境准备映像（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-"
"image-preparation-airgap\"/>）</emphasis>：此步骤用于显示差异，以准备好要在隔"
"离场景中使用的清单和文件。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2074
msgid ""
"Directory structure for air-gap environments (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-"
"directory-structure-airgap\"/>): The directory structure must be modified to "
"include the resources needed to run the management cluster in an air-gap "
"environment."
msgstr ""
"隔离环境的目录结构（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-directory-structure-airgap"
"\"/>）：必须修改目录结构，以包含用于在隔离环境中运行管理群集的资源。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2075
msgid ""
"Modifications in the definition file (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-image-"
"definition-file-airgap\"/>): The <literal>mgmt-cluster.yaml</literal> file "
"must be modified to include the <literal>embeddedArtifactRegistry</literal> "
"section with the <literal>images</literal> field set to all container images "
"to be included into the EIB output image."
msgstr ""
"定义文件中的修改（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-image-definition-file-airgap"
"\"/>）：必须修改 <literal>mgmt-cluster.yaml</literal> 文件，以包含 "
"<literal>embeddedArtifactRegistry</literal> 部分，并将 <literal>images</"
"literal> 字段设置为要包含在 EIB 输出映像中的所有容器映像。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2076
msgid ""
"Modifications in the custom folder (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-custom-"
"folder-airgap\"/>): The <literal>custom</literal> folder must be modified to "
"include the resources needed to run the management cluster in an air-gap "
"environment."
msgstr ""
"custom 文件夹中的修改（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-custom-folder-airgap\"/"
">）：必须修改 <literal>custom</literal> 文件夹，以包含用于在隔离环境中运行管"
"理群集的资源。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2077
msgid ""
"Register script: The <literal>custom/scripts/99-register.sh</literal> script "
"must be removed when you use an air-gap environment."
msgstr ""
"注册脚本：使用隔离环境时，必须去除 <literal>custom/scripts/99-register.sh</"
"literal> 脚本。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2078
msgid ""
"Air-gap resources: The <literal>custom/files/airgap-resources.tar.gz</"
"literal> file must be included in the <literal>custom/files</literal> folder "
"with all the resources needed to run the management cluster in an air-gap "
"environment."
msgstr ""
"隔离资源：必须在 <literal>custom/files</literal> 文件夹中包含 "
"<literal>custom/files/airgap-resources.tar.gz</literal> 文件，该文件包含用于"
"在隔离环境中运行管理群集的所有资源。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2079
msgid ""
"Scripts: The <literal>custom/scripts/99-mgmt-setup.sh</literal> script must "
"be modified to extract and copy the <literal>airgap-resources.tar.gz</"
"literal> file to the final location. The <literal>custom/files/metal3.sh</"
"literal> script must be modified to use the local resources included in the "
"<literal>airgap-resources.tar.gz</literal> file instead of downloading them "
"from the internet."
msgstr ""
"脚本：必须修改 <literal>custom/scripts/99-mgmt-setup.sh</literal> 脚本，以提"
"取 <literal>airgap-resources.tar.gz</literal> 文件并将其复制到最终位置。必须"
"修改 <literal>custom/files/metal3.sh</literal> 脚本，以使用 <literal>airgap-"
"resources.tar.gz</literal> 文件中包含的本地资源，而不是从互联网下载资源。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2080
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Image creation (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-image-"
"creation\"/>)</emphasis>: This step covers the creation of the image using "
"the Edge Image Builder tool (for both, connected and air-gap scenarios). "
"Check the prerequisites (<xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/>) to run the Edge "
"Image Builder tool on your system."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">创建映像（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-image-"
"creation\"/>）</emphasis>：此步骤使用 Edge Image Builder 工具创建映像（适用于"
"联网场景和隔离场景）。在系统上运行 Edge Image Builder 工具之前请先检查先决条"
"件（<xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/>）。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2081
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Management Cluster Provision (<xref linkend=\"mgmt-"
"cluster-provision\"/>)</emphasis>: This step covers the provisioning of the "
"management cluster using the image created in the previous step (for both, "
"connected and air-gap scenarios). This step can be done using a laptop, "
"server, VM or any other x86_64 system with a USB port."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">置备管理群集（<xref linkend=\"mgmt-cluster-"
"provision\"/>）</emphasis>：此步骤使用上一步骤中创建的映像来置备管理群集（适"
"用于联网场景和隔离场景）。可以使用便携式计算机、服务器、VM 或任何其他带有 "
"USB 端口的 x86_64 系统来执行此步骤。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2082
msgid ""
"For more information about Edge Image Builder, see Edge Image Builder (<xref "
"linkend=\"components-eib\"/>) and Edge Image Builder Quick Start (<xref "
"linkend=\"quickstart-eib\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"有关 Edge Image Builder 的详细信息，请参见 Edge Image Builder（<xref linkend="
"\"components-eib\"/>）和 Edge Image Builder 快速入门（<xref linkend="
"\"quickstart-eib\"/>）。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2083
msgid "Image preparation for connected environments"
msgstr "为联网环境准备映像"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2084
msgid ""
"Using Edge Image Builder to create the image for the management cluster, a "
"lot of configurations can be customized, but in this document, we cover the "
"minimal configurations necessary to set up the management cluster.  Edge "
"Image Builder is typically run from inside a container so, if you do not "
"already have a way to run containers, we need to start by installing a "
"container runtime such as <link xl:href=\"https://podman.io\">Podman</link> "
"or <link xl:href=\"https://rancherdesktop.io\">Rancher Desktop</link>. For "
"this guide, we assume you already have a container runtime available."
msgstr ""
"使用 Edge Image Builder 为管理群集创建映像时可以自定义许多配置，但本文档只会"
"介绍设置管理群集所需的最低限度配置。Edge Image Builder 通常从容器内部运行，因"
"此，如果您目前无法运行容器，则首先需要安装 <link xl:href=\"https://podman.io"
"\">Podman</link> 或 <link xl:href=\"https://rancherdesktop.io\">Rancher "
"Desktop</link> 之类的容器运行时。本指南假设您已经安装了可用的容器运行时。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2085
msgid ""
"Also, as a prerequisite to deploy a highly available management cluster, you "
"need to reserve three IPs in your network: - <literal>apiVIP</literal> for "
"the API VIP Address (used to access the Kubernetes API server).  - "
"<literal>ingressVIP</literal> for the Ingress VIP Address (consumed, for "
"example, by the Rancher UI).  - <literal>metal3VIP</literal> for the Metal3 "
"VIP Address."
msgstr ""
"此外，作为部署高可用性管理群集的先决条件，您需要在网络中预留三个 IP：- "
"<literal>apiVIP</literal>（表示 API VIP 地址，用于访问 Kubernetes API 服务"
"器）。- <literal>ingressVIP</literal>（表示入口 VIP 地址，由 Rancher UI 等组"
"件使用）。- <literal>metal3VIP</literal>（表示 Metal3 VIP 地址）。"

